data.introduction:
Spanning four Provinces – Nakhon Ratchasima, Prachin Buri, Nakhon Nayok, and Saraburi – Khao Yai National Park is renowned
for its diverse flora and fauna, including elephants, deer, gaur, and barking deer frequently sighted. The park is a source of several rivers, including the Nakhon Nayok, Prachin Buri, Lamtakong, Lam Praploeng,
and Huai Mawak.
